display_title = "The Night, Again"
text = "Gabe pockets his lighter and his pipe and takes out a flask from his pocket, then he approaches the wall where the shadows dance. He opens his arms wide, and starts to sing in a voice that feels totally unfamiliar to you now:

[GABE]: Weathervane, Weathervane, won't you come play?

[GABE]: Weathervane, Weathervane, I hope you don't stay!

He repeats this a few times, and in some deep, judgmental part of yourself you wonder: Is this it? A stoned man singing a silly rhyme at a wall? If Gabe's magical creature really existed, it would probably be too embarassed to show itself.

But then...
"
